1)  🔹 CSV
Explanation
Row-based
Plain text
No schema (all strings by default)
💻 Example
df = spark.read.csv("file.csv", header=True)
🧠 Scenario

👉 Reads entire file even if you need 1 column ❌

🔹 Parquet
Explanation
Columnar format
Compressed
Schema stored
💻 Example
df = spark.read.parquet("file.parquet")
🧠 Scenario

👉 Reads only required columns ✔
👉 Faster queries ✔

🔹 ORC
Explanation
Columnar format (similar to Parquet)
Highly optimized for Hive
💻 Example
df = spark.read.orc("file.orc")

CSV is a row-based text format with no schema and slower performance, whereas Parquet and ORC are columnar formats that support compression, schema, and predicate pushdown, making them much faster and efficient for big data processing

